Is anyone here using a light/sunrise alarm clock to get up in the morning for work? I've heard you tend to wake up way more energized and less stressed with one than using a standard phone alarm. Seems way more neutral and probably good for circadian health and hormonal cycles...

I think they basically simulate a sunrise's light environment so your body prepares to wake up while you're still sleeping. Sort of like if a red light chicken light was also an alarm clock. I think Philips made the original ones, Northernlion talked about it way back in the day.
What brand/model are you using?

I wonder if they've done actual studies with them and how using one would impact stuff like morning cortisol levels. The more I think about it the more the biological mechanism for a light alarm clock seems really sensible.

There's this experiment that Dr. Michael Persinger talked about in "No More Secrets" where a sleeping man's dreams were influenced by the thoughts of another person in a different room. Imagine how much sleeping with another person in the same bed will influence your dreams then.
